00047 /**
00048  * translateEngineMessageHandlingCallBack
00049  * Synopsis:
00050  *
00051  *  There is a catch 22 where the command line message handlers need to
00052  * have the PGOptions information in order to set up the message handling
00053  * log file name, etc. Resolve this by passing in a call back to the
00054  * TranslateEngine constructor which initializes the PGOptions.
00055  *
00056  * @param atdOopts - filled in with all the PGOptions data.
00057  *
00058  * @return - nada, initializes message handling.
00059  */
00060 /*****************************************************************************/
00061 static void translateEngineMessageHandlingCallBack(ADTOptions & adtOpts)
00062 {
00063 
00064   Err::setThrowStatus(true);
00065 
00066   string verboseLogName = Fs::join(adtOpts.m_outputDir,adtOpts.m_progName+".log");
00067 
00068   std::ofstream *verboseOFStream = new std::ofstream;
00069 
00070   Fs::mustOpenToWrite(*(verboseOFStream), verboseLogName.c_str());
00071 
00072   ADT_VERBOSE_ENUM logVerbosity = ADT_VERBOSE_EXCEPTION;
00073   if (adtOpts.m_verbosity > ADT_VERBOSE_EXCEPTION) {
00074     logVerbosity = (ADT_VERBOSE_ENUM) adtOpts.m_verbosity;
00075   }
00076 
00077   LogStream *verboseLogStream = new
00078   LogStream(logVerbosity,  verboseOFStream);
00079 
00080   Verbose::pushMsgHandler(verboseLogStream);
00081   Verbose::pushProgressHandler(verboseLogStream);
00082   Verbose::pushWarnHandler(verboseLogStream);
00083   Verbose::setLevel(adtOpts.m_verbosity);
00084 
00085   return;
00086 }
00087 // end translateEngineMessageHandlingCallBack
